## Dates and Times in Python

## Importing  

	import datetime


## datetime.datetime.now()
Gives a breakdown of the time.
	
	>>> datetime.datetime.now()
	datetime.datetime(2016, 2, 9, 21, 18, 51, 494859)

## datetime.datetime.replace()
Gives the option of replacing datetime variables

	timevar = datetime.datetime.now()
	timevar = timevar.replace(hour=9, second=0, minute=0, second=0, microsecond=0)
	

## Timedelta	

